Should the coronavirus pandemic disrupt that event along with other tournaments, Goudy is prepared to view the Amateur Athletic Union’s financial losses as significant.
Communities with sprawling, empty fields and arenas are losing millions of dollars with lucrative tournaments canceled or postponed.
Thousands of youth leagues are on hold, with many sponsors hit by the economic slowdown and the prospect of nervous parents seeking refunds.
Officials and experts are estimating tens of millions of dollars in losses for youth sports facilities because of the shutdown.
“I don’t think there’s any question that’s going to rebound.”Copyright © The Associated Press.